The paper presents a neural approach to the Story Cloze Test, which involves natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses skip-thought embeddings and a feed-forward network, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves training a model and achieving high accuracy, which are common themes in neural networks and optimization, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with text and language understanding, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
